The berserker's guarantedd crit of from 1-99% will normalize over time to about 50% bonus damage, with the loss of parry and evade ability.  The blademaster's triple-wield grants them guaranteed 50% bonus damage (essentially equivalent to the zerker bonus damage), and immunity from crits.  So those 2 abilities in particular are completely unbalanced.  Berserkers get 50% bonus damage, and lose of parry and evade, blademasters get 50% bonus damage and immunity to crits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=halbaradaglardin>Halbarad Aglardin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#000000>(4/27/03 11:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.arador.de/halklein.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Removing defense penalties from frenzy</span><hr size=1> I have to agree...<br>
